Russia said there were no survivors after Kyiv had downed the Il-76 plane with 65 Ukrainian prisoners of war, six Russian crew and three escorts.
 
Moscow claimed the Ukrainians were being flown for a prisoner exchange.
 
Ukraine's military intelligence (GUR) said it had not been told to ensure safe airspace, as on previous occasions.

recommandationVideos.Title: Is the West leaving Ukraine out to dry? | To the point
recommandationVideos.Description:
For NATO, a worst-case scenario would be a Russian attack on one of its member states. Now it’s rehearsing for exactly that possibility: running its biggest military drills since the Cold War to practice its response.

The exercise, called Steadfast Defender, sees some 90,000 troops from 32 countries taking part with fighter jets, tanks, and warships: all shortly before the second anniversary of Russia’s full-scale invasion of Ukraine. Since then, Kyiv has fought to expel its invaders with help from Western weapon deliveries: but will the support continue? Today on To The Point we’re looking at Putin’s imperial ambitions, asking: Is the West leaving Ukraine out to dry?

recommandationVideos.Title: Did China Crack the F-35's Stealth Code? Implications for Air Warfare
recommandationVideos.Description:
Did China Crack the F-35's Stealth Code? Implications for Air Warfare

🛩️ Greetings, fellow aviation enthusiasts! Today, we delve into a sensitive topic: the alleged compromise of the F-35's vaunted stealth technology. A leaked document has ignited anxieties, raising crucial questions about the future of air warfare. So, strap yourselves in as we dissect the intel and explore the potential ramifications.

A Legacy of Lethal Secrets
Weapons technology thrives on secrecy, and the F-35 embodies this principle like no other aircraft. Its stealth capabilities, akin to an air-borne invisibility cloak, have been a cornerstone of American air dominance for years. From evading radars to striking unseen, the F-35 has redefined aerial combat.

But whispers of China's interest in this forbidden fruit have swirled for years. Suspicious espionage cases and the emergence of China's J-20, bearing an uncanny resemblance to the F-35, only fueled the speculation.

The Leaked Pandora's Box
Now, a leaked document has thrown open the doors to this classified cockpit. Imagine finding the blueprints to Fort Knox casually delivered to your doorstep! This document reportedly contains detailed information on the F-35's radar signature, material composition, and potentially, even deeper secrets.

Is the F-35 Toast? Not So Fast.
Before we sound the alarm bells, let's remember that stealth is a multi-layered onion. While China might have peeled back a few outer layers, the core – the truly classified and most effective technology – likely remains under impregnable lock and key. Replicating such advanced stealth capabilities demands not just the knowledge, but also the precise manufacturing techniques and exotic materials, areas where China is still playing catch-up.

However, a Compromised Onion Still Bites
Even a partially compromised stealth system can pose serious threats. This leak could grant China the ability to detect and target F-35s at significantly longer ranges, a game-changer in aerial combat. The US will need to adapt its tactics and rethink its reliance on this once-impenetrable shield.

The Murky Future of Air Warfare
The landscape of air warfare has just shifted dramatically. Will the F-35 evolve, regaining its cloak of invisibility? Will China's J-20 finally live up to its "Dragon Lady" moniker, challenging American supremacy in the skies? These are the questions that now haunt the minds of military strategists and fighter pilots alike.

Remember, knowledge is power, and in the ever-evolving arena of aviation, staying informed is crucial. So, hit that subscribe button, smash that notification bell, and join us on this thrilling journey through the skies of tomorrow!

Ukraine is yet to officially claim responsibility.

It has attacked four other oil depots in Russia this month, including one in St Petersburg more than 700 miles from Ukraine’s northern border.

recommandationVideos.Title: Eugene Kenneth Smith: First person executed with nitrogen gas took 22 minutes to die
recommandationVideos.Description:
An Alabama prisoner who became the first person to ever be executed using nitrogen gas took 22 minutes to die despite the state promising his death would be quick and painless.

Kenneth Smith shook and writhed for two minutes on Thursday night as his mask filled up with the gas, witnesses said.

The convicted killer is said to have remained conscious, breathing heavily and gasping for a further eight minutes as his sons and crying wife watched on.

Smith, 58, was not pronounced dead until 8.25pm, 22 minutes after the gas was first administered.

But Steve Marshall, Alabama’s attorney general, insisted that the execution had “proved” nitrogen gas was “an effective and humane method of execution”.

recommandationVideos.Title: What To Do With All The Empty Offices In U.S. Cities | CNBC Marathon
recommandationVideos.Description:
Now that the remote and hybrid work revolution has begun, many cities are filled with empty or half empty offices, creating very quiet downtowns. At the same time, the U.S. is experiencing a housing crisis. CNBC Marathon explores if U.S. cities will convert offices into apartments.

Some U.S. mayors are loosening up rules that determine how developers convert office buildings into apartment complexes. The conversion trend sped up in the 2020s, as the pandemic remote work boom reshaped cities. Declines in office activity are straining tax revenues for city services like education and transit, leading some local leaders to prioritize increased conversion of dated buildings. These rule changes may create some additional housing supply in regions like the U.S. east coast.

Meanwhile, San Francisco is facing its highest office vacancy rates in nearly 30 years. At the same time, the city is facing a housing crisis with the state demanding 82,000 new units of housing to be built by 2031. CNBC sits down with San Francisco Mayor London Breed to discuss how the city could tackle two of its biggest issues head-on. Plus, CNBC visits a building in the Civic Center neighborhood that undertook the biggest office-to-residential conversion in the city to date.

Major American cities such as New York and San Francisco face serious problems — mass migration, empty offices and declining tax revenues. These trends have had a direct impact on cities, which rely on tax revenues for funding, a significant portion from commercial real estate. recommandationVideos.Title: How Scharnhorst was Sunk: Battle of the North Cape 1943
recommandationVideos.Description:
In December 1943, in the darkest years of the Second World War at Christmas time, one of the Kriegsmarine's few lethal remaining surface warships was sent on the hunt to win a propaganda victory for the German war effort. Arctic convoy JW55B was headed for Murmansk but was being stalked by Scharnhorst, 5 destroyers and 6 U-Boats. The Germans closed in for the kill - but they didn't know they were steaming straight into a trap. Admiral Bruce Fraser had brought the might of the British Royal Navy to bear including the guns of his flagship HMS Duke of York. Together with the cruiser HMS Belfast, Norfolk, Jamaica and others the German warship would be engaged and destroyed after years of wreaking havoc in the Atlantic. This is the remarkable true story of the battleship Scharnhorst, her sister Gneisenau and the remarkable events that led to the legendary ship's sinking.

Please note: this film is not intended to glorify the Third Reich nor any of its genocidal political motivations but rather to serve as a tribute to the sailors of all nationalities who lost their lives at sea in those dark years 1939-1945. All imagery and material used in this film is within a purely historical and immersive context.

recommandationVideos.Title: How Scharnhorst was Sunk: Battle of the North Cape 1943
recommandationVideos.Description:
In December 1943, in the darkest years of the Second World War at Christmas time, one of the Kriegsmarine's few lethal remaining surface warships was sent on the hunt to win a propaganda victory for the German war effort. Arctic convoy JW55B was headed for Murmansk but was being stalked by Scharnhorst, 5 destroyers and 6 U-Boats. The Germans closed in for the kill - but they didn't know they were steaming straight into a trap. Admiral Bruce Fraser had brought the might of the British Royal Navy to bear including the guns of his flagship HMS Duke of York. Together with the cruiser HMS Belfast, Norfolk, Jamaica and others the German warship would be engaged and destroyed after years of wreaking havoc in the Atlantic. This is the remarkable true story of the battleship Scharnhorst, her sister Gneisenau and the remarkable events that led to the legendary ship's sinking.

Please note: this film is not intended to glorify the Third Reich nor any of its genocidal political motivations but rather to serve as a tribute to the sailors of all nationalities who lost their lives at sea in those dark years 1939-1945. All imagery and material used in this film is within a purely historical and immersive context.

This film was written by Joseph Lavender and edited by Michael Brady.
Animated by Jack Gibson.
3D models by Thomas Beerens via Sketchfab.

recommandationVideos.Description:
Коли стало відомо, що Україна отримає сотню танків Leopard 1, постало питання, як їх застосовуватимуть на фронті. Leopard 1А5 розробляли з огляду на Холодну війну і можливе застосування ядерної зброї на полі бою, тому перевага віддавалася рухливості над захистом. Мовляв, від ядерної зброї все одно ніщо не врятує. В умовах російсько-української війни тонка броня танка є його значним недоліком. Це зазначають і танкісти, які отримали їх на озброєння. Але вони вже оцінили інші переваги — маневровість, рухливість і швидкість. Механік-водій Хом’як, говорить, що танк назад розганяється швидше, ніж Т-64 уперед, на якому він раніше працював. На «леопарді» танкіст їздить до 50 км/год.
Крім того, як розповідає навідник Владислав, він може влучати з 90% впевненістю у ціль на відстані 3,5 км.
«Вона [гармата] на великій дальності буде досить ефективно працювати. Приціл дозволяє, тепловізійний приціл так само дозволяє [працювати] уночі», — розповідає про переваги Leopard 1 командир взводу Олександр.
Військовий додає: хоча гармата у Leopard 1 меншого калібру — 105 мм, — вона також може пробивати сучасні російські танки.
Про те, як українські танкісти застосовуватимуть Leopard 1 у боях, — детальніше в репортажі Діани Буцко та Миколи Пастуха.

recommandationVideos.Title: Talvisota 🇫🇮
recommandationVideos.Description:
Talvisota käytiin 30.11.1939-13.3.1940 Suomen ja Neuvostoliiton välillä! Sota kesti ainoastaan 105 päivää ja päättyi Moskovan rauhansopimukseen! Talvisodassa suomalaiset sotilaat taistelivat urheasti ylivoimaisen vihollisen kanssa. Suomalaisten sisukkuutta on kuvattu talvisodan henki -nimityksellä.

Ennen talvisotaa tilanne Euroopassa oli kiristynyt merkittävästi. Hitler ja Stalin olivat hämmästyttäneet maailmaa sopimalla keskenään hyökkäämättömyyssopimuksen. Suomi oli joutunut kahden suurvallan, Saksan ja Neuvostoliiton pelinappulaksi maiden keskinäisessä hyökkäämättömyyssopimuksen salaisessa lisäpöytäkirjassa.

Neuvostoliitto syytti Suomea talvisodan aloittamisesta kuuluisissa Mainilan laukauksissa. Todellisuudessa tämä oli Neuvostoliiton itsensä järjestämä selkkaus, joka antoi sille syyn aloittaa sodan Suomea vastaan!

Talvisodan aikaan Suomen puolustusvoimien ylipäällikkö oli Carl Gustaf Emil Mannerheim, jolla oli kokemusta tsaarin armeijan upseerina olemisesta. Päämajansa Mannerheim perusti Mikkeliin.

Talvisota käytiin erityisen haastavissa olosuhteissa ja pakkanen painui jopa -40 asteeseen. Tämä oli varsinkin Neuvostoliittolaisille sotilailla kova paikka, sillä he oli lähetetty matkaan pääosin kesävaatteissa ja ilman talvisaappaita. Myöskään hiihtäminen ei ollut puna-armeijalle tuttua.

Tällä videolla käsitellään Talvisodan isojen linojen lisäksi esimerkiksi hyökkäystä Toivajärvelle ja maailmallakin tunnettua Raatteentien taistelua. Lisäksi paneudutaan niihin syihin, jotka lopulta johtivat siihen, että Suomi joutui luovuttamaan Neuvostoliitolle massiiviset maa-alueet.

If you mentioned BMW to most people, they think of a car. They don't think of something with an engine of 1,800 horsepower powering one of the deadliest fighters of the Second World War. The Focke-Wulf 190.

Kurt Tank's design of the Focke-Wulf 190 was hunched like a pitbull. Very strong in design. Tapered wing edges. It could roll very fast. It could take a lot of punishment. And the performance was electrifying.

In this video, IWM Duxford's Graham Rodgers explored the history of Germany's 'Butcher Bird'.

recommandationVideos.Title: Inside Rural Russia: When Military and Patriotism Are Your Life | ENDEVR Documentary
recommandationVideos.Description:
Inside Rural Russia: When Military and Patriotism Are Your Life | Town of Glory | ENDEVR Documentary

Watch 'The Oligarch's Wife - Married to a Hunted Russian Billionaire' here: https://youtu.be/QCJpX2nhY3Q

A heroic Soviet past and a destitute post-industrial present make the provincial town of Yenya susceptible to the Kremlin's aggressive anti-Western propaganda leading to the militarization of society from kindergarten to pension age. With few exceptions, Yelnyans raise their children to become good patriots. They don’t mind the eerie, all-encompassing militarization of society.

Filmed over the course of three years, this film introduces Western viewers to the small and prototypical provincial Russian town of Yelnya where people admire Vladimir Putin for making Russia great again. Yelnya has remained economically marginalized ever since the Soviet Union collapsed. But people have regained pride. They believe that President Putin is bringing back glory and power to the Russian nation. Not many object to the constant propaganda claims that fascism is threatening once again from the US and Europe and that Russia must stand ready to defend itself.

recommandationVideos.Title: Suomalaistaistelijan haastattelu, Kramatorsk, Ukraina, 2.3.2023.
recommandationVideos.Description:
Autamme Ukrainassa olevia suomalaisia kouluttajia ja legioonalaisia keräämällä heille tarvitsemiaan varusteita ja autoja, järjestämällä heidät haluamaansa palveluspaikkaan ja tuomalla Suomeen hoitoon haavoittumisen sattuessa. Tällä reissulla saimme tuotua Ukrainan puolustusvoimissa palveleville suomalaisille mm. Vortexin punapistetähtäimiä ja etäisyysmittarin, kymmeniä ensiapupakkauksia ja kiristyssiteitä, kuivamuonaa, CPT Cartridge Package Tactical -lipastajia, sekä tietysti kotimaista Reissumies ruisleipää ja Atrian Gotler-makkaraa…

Samassa yhteydessä Suomi-Ukraina Maanpuolustusyhdistyksen perustajalle, Kirill Rinteelle myönnettiin sotasaaliina saatu harvinainen yhdistyksen komentajan pistimeksi nimitetty Tokarevin pistin.

Keräämme seuraavaa lähetystä varten maastoajoon soveltuvia ajoneuvoja, taktisia suojavarusteita, maastokenkiä, pimeänäkölaitteita, lämpö-, punapiste- ja kiikaritähtäimiä, taktisia ensiapupakkauksia - jos ei ole varma, mitä ostaa, niin voi osallistua meidän keräykseen - tarkempaa tietoa nettisivuillamme www.sumpy.fi.

Yhdistyksemme jäsenet ovat vieneet rintamalle maastopukuja, luoti- ja taisteluliivejä, kypäriä, sotilasradioita, kiikari-, punapiste-, lämpötähtäimiä, maastokenkiä, naamiointiverkkoja, droneja, villasukkia, vaatteita, Sky Wiper dronekiväärin yms. Olemme sodan aikana evakuoineet Ukrainasta 3 haavoittunutta suomalaista legioonalaista ja kymmeniä pakolaisperheitä. Kyllästyneinä viranomaisten saamattomuuteen toimme ensimmäisinä Suomeen hoitoon toistakymmentä haavoittunutta erikoisyksikön sotilasta Harkovasta kesällä 2022. 

Yhdistyksemme on myös auttanut ukrainalaisia yrityksiä saamaan tuotteensa myyntiin Suomessa, esitellyt lukuisia suomalaisia aseteollisuuden yrityksiä Ukrainan erikoisjoukoille ja järjestänyt heidän tuotteita testattavaksi erikoisjoukkojen käyttöön, sekä pannut alulle lukuisia ukrainalaisia auttavia ja suomalaisia työllistäviä rakennusteollisuuden projekteja.

Toimimme aina operatiivisesti ja viemme tarvikkeet suorinta ja nopeinta reittiä, vaikka rintamalle. 
Tiimimme on sitoutunut tekemään kaikkensa sen eteen, että Ukraina selviää sodasta voittajana. 
Kaikki, jotka kokevat meidän arvot omakseen - tervetuloa mukaan yhdistyksemme toimintaan.

recommandationVideos.Title: Russian oil refinery burns after Ukrainian drone strike as factories are torched
recommandationVideos.Description:
A massive oil refinery in Russia burst into flames after being struck by a long-range Ukrainian drone, in the latest attack of its kind. The Tuapse refinery, located around 250 miles from the frontline, burned for several hours before the fire could be extinguished. More footage showed what appeared to be a drone heading for the refinery, after apparently being launched from Ukraine. Meanwhile three factories, two of them located more than 2,000 miles from Ukraine, were also set on fire, which has also become a common occurrence. Tuapse produces about 240,000 barrels of oil per day and is mainly used to supply Turkey, China, and Singapore.
